# Festag — desktop auth pages locked

Desktop **Login** and **Register** (`AuthLandingPage` + shared `auth-landing-styles`) are settled.

## Do not

- Restyle, reflow, or “polish” those desktop surfaces unprompted
- Change CTA, input, tip, agreements, or chrome look “while you’re here”
- Broad auth CSS edits that alter desktop Login/Register appearance without an explicit ask

## Do

- Only touch them when the user **explicitly** names Login/Register (or a concrete control on those pages)
- Shared tokens/logic fixes that must land for other routes are fine if desktop look stays identical — prefer scoping to Dev/onboarding/mobile when possible
